<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> sony needs to change it's policy and provide more solo ability to wizards or better access to our higher nooks.. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
What does solo ability have to do with better nukes? Wouldn't it make more sense to replace better nukes with more group friendly spells?<br>
<br>
Verant has already stated that balancing involves 3 things. A) Soloing B) Grouping C) Raiding. The trick is, if you increase a wizard's power in one field then you also increase our power in yet another. <br>
<br>
Giving a wizard better solo abilities such as stronger roots in order to root nuke, higher mana regen, more efficient nukes, well that also rolls over into grouping <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>and</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> raiding better b/c you can root park easier, nuke more often, and again nuke more often.<br>
<br>
If they give us easier access to our better nukes then theres yet another problem, b/c not only do you increase raiding dramatically our grouping situation becomes a whole lot easier, and not only that soloing is now even easier with our better nukes.<br>
<br>
So your statement of <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> sony needs to change it's policy and provide more solo ability to wizards or better access to our higher nooks.. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> cannot be done. It is makes us too powerful in all 3 areas of what the designers see as most important parts of balancing.<br>
